{
  "text": "The United Kingdom Prospective Diabetes Study (UKPDS) is a series of studies of diabetes. The original study in 1998 enrolled 5,102 patients with newly diagnosed type 2 diabetes. [CITATION_1] The more than 1,000 patients with hypertension were randomized to either tight blood pressure Diabetic nephropathy progression is a one-way street Urine albumin excretion rate (mg/24 h) < 30 30-300 > 300",
